arguments.new_str:
{
  "configProperties": {
    "System.GC.Server": true,
    "System.Threading.ThreadPool.MinThreads": 50
  },
  "$schema": "https://json.schemastore.org/dotnet-runtimeconfig.json",
  "_comment": "BREAKING CHANGE in .NET 9: Environment variables now take precedence over runtimeconfig.json values. Our Kubernetes env vars DOTNET_gcServer=0 and DOTNET_ThreadPool_MinThreads=4 will now override the values above. In .NET 8 these runtimeconfig values won, so behavior was Server GC + 50 min threads. In .NET 9 the env vars win, giving Workstation GC + 4 min threads. If that is the intended behavior, no further action is needed. If you want to preserve .NET 8 behavior, REMOVE those env vars from your K8s deployment."
}

